overview: The user aimed to enhance their Sleep Questionnaire Application by
  adding a database for storing responses and an admin dashboard for data
  access. The assistant evaluated the existing codebase, identified the missing
  components, and developed a comprehensive plan. Key decisions included using
  NeonDB (PostgreSQL) with Prisma for database management and implementing a
  simple password-based authentication system. The plan involved updating
  demographic data fields, creating a Prisma model for questionnaire responses,
  developing API routes for saving and retrieving data (including CSV export),
  and building the admin dashboard. During implementation, the authentication
  system was refined to leverage Next.js middleware for cleaner route
  protection. The assistant also provided detailed instructions for database
  setup and initiated browser-based testing to confirm all new functionalities
  were working as expected.
